BAGGAGE:
The free baggage allowance for each domestic route
passenger paying full or half adult fare is as follows:
Passenger paying first category domestic fare: 20kg.
for first class; 15kg. for economy class.
Passenger paying second category domestic fare: 30
kg. for first class; 20kg. for economy class.
Baggage in excess of the free baggage allowance will
be charged at the excess baggage rate.
For each international passenger paying full or half
adult fare, the free baggage allowances will be as follows:
30kg. for first class; 20kg. for economy class. On CAAC
China-U.S. flights, the free baggage allowance for each
passenger paying full or half adult fare is two pieces of
baggage, each not exceeding 32kg.
In addition, each
passenger may carry in his own custody a handbag, an
overcoat,
an umbrella or walking stick, a reasonable
amount of reading material for the flight, infant's food
for consumption en route, infant's carrying basket and
a fully collapsible invalid's wheelchair.
No free baggage allowance is granted to an infant
paying 10% of the adult fare.
PIECE METHOD:
The piece method would apply for most inter-
national travel between points in the U.S.A. and points
outside the U.S.A. The free baggage allowance is de-
termined by the number of pieces of checked and/or
unchecked baggage provided
the sum of the linear
measurements (length/width/height) does not exceed
a specified measurement and is within a specified weight
limitation.
